Text: Just overheard the latest on the LatAm economic summit—Brazil's taking the lead, claiming he can cook a better asado while I challenge him to a tango-off!
As usual, I’m pushing for financial independence, but all they want to discuss is exporting more soy.
And don’t even get me started on Chile; she tried to throw shade over our Patagonia claims during the group chat—classic.
I’ll just remind her who holds the World Cup bragging rights, right after I perfect my mate-brewing technique while dodging serious topics with a little dance.
Chile tried to flex her Patagonia muscles again—classic!
I mean, who doesn't love a good dance-off over territorial disputes?
Meanwhile, the LatAm summit felt like a soccer match where Brazil claimed the asado crown, but you know I’m better at both grilling and grooving.
Financial independence still feels like a distant dream as everyone hops on the soy train—can’t they see the real profit lies in gourmet mate blends?
If I had a peso for every time I had to remind them about World Cup glory… eh, would still be less stressful than this chat.
